<paragraph id="E97036DD3F7AFFEDFF76FD8EFC8FFDC3" blockId="79.[151,1437,520,1194]" box="[151,879,520,547]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">
Size. Maximum size 2.0 cm total length (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F7AFFEDFD85FD8EFC83FDC3" author="Engin, S. &amp; Seyhan, D." box="[612,867,520,546]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" pagination="1208 - 1223" refId="ref53814" refString="Engin, S. &amp; Seyhan, D. (2017) A new species of Pomatoschistus (Teleostei, Gobiidae): the Mediterraneans smallest marine fish. Journal of Fish Biology, 91, 1208 - 1223. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jfb. 13455" type="journal article" year="2017">Engin &amp; Seyhan 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A1D565563F7AFFEDFF26FDAAFE49FB4B" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" type="description">
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F7AFFEDFF26FDAAFEC9FD37" blockId="79.[151,1437,520,1194]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">
Morphology. D VI + I,8; A I,9–11; P 15–16 (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F7AFFEDFD53FDAAFC4EFDA7" author="Engin, S. &amp; Seyhan, D." box="[690,942,556,582]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" pagination="1208 - 1223" refId="ref53814" refString="Engin, S. &amp; Seyhan, D. (2017) A new species of Pomatoschistus (Teleostei, Gobiidae): the Mediterraneans smallest marine fish. Journal of Fish Biology, 91, 1208 - 1223. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jfb. 13455" type="journal article" year="2017">Engin &amp; Seyhan 2017</bibRefCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F7AFFEDFC5EFDAAFB9DFDA7" bold="true" box="[959,1149,556,582]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">Very small goby</emphasis>
with subcylindrical body, laterally compressed towards caudal fin, head slightly depressed and moderately small. Snout pointed. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F7AFFEDFAF8FDD6FA7CFD8B" bold="true" box="[1305,1436,592,618]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">Eyes large.</emphasis>
Caudal peduncle slender, lower than body depth. Dorsal fins of similar height, the first dorsal fin with more or less rounded margin and no elongated spines. Caudal fin slightly emarginate. Scales present, but not usually visible on photographs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F7AFFEDFF26FD66FF02FC16" blockId="79.[151,1437,520,1194]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">
Live coloration. Body mostly translucent (
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F7AFFEDFD46FD66FD1BFD1A" box="[679,763,736,763]" captionStart="FIGURE 68" captionStartId="79.[151,250,2009,2033]" captionTargetBox="[218,1369,1218,1985]" captionTargetId="figure-388@79.[218,1369,1218,1985]" captionTargetPageId="79" captionText="FIGURE 68. Live coloration in its natural habitat of Pomatoschistus nanus. Photo by S. Engin, Kaş, Antalya, Turkey." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601771" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601771/files/figure.png" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">Fig. 68</figureCitation>
); 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F7AFFEDFCF0FD66FDB1FCFF" bold="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">most visible chromatophores are deep inside the body, arranged along the vertebral column</emphasis>
in a white line interspersed with dark markings and then, three longer dark lines and finally an elongate spot on caudal-fin base. Superimposed on this deep pattern are 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F7AFFEDFB23FCAEFC90FC87" bold="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">4 very thin dorsal white saddles and a fifth broader saddle on caudal peduncle</emphasis>
; a midlateral dark spot, that may slightly extend ventrally, below each saddle. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F7AFFEDFE05FCF6FA75FC6B" bold="true" box="[484,1429,880,906]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">Body whitish ventrally, with vertical, iridescent, pale gray streaks. Cheeks pale</emphasis>
. Usually no horizontal Y-shaped dark marking on opercle. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F7AFFEDFCFAFC12FBD9FC33" bold="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">On nape, 3 whitish to white markings just behind eyes with 2 dark longitudinal streaks in between, and underlined with dark on sides</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F7AFFEDFBA7FC3EFAA0FC33" author="Engin, S. &amp; Seyhan, D." box="[1094,1344,952,978]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" pagination="1208 - 1223" refId="ref53814" refString="Engin, S. &amp; Seyhan, D. (2017) A new species of Pomatoschistus (Teleostei, Gobiidae): the Mediterraneans smallest marine fish. Journal of Fish Biology, 91, 1208 - 1223. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jfb. 13455" type="journal article" year="2017">Engin &amp; Seyhan 2017</bibRefCitation>
; present work).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F7AFFEDFF26FB86FCBDFBFA" blockId="79.[151,1437,520,1194]" box="[199,861,1024,1051]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">
Similar species. 
<taxonomicName id="2ECF4D5E3F7AFFEDFE9EFB86FD90FBFB" authorityName="Miller" authorityYear="1982" box="[383,624,1024,1050]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Pomatoschistus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bathi">
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F7AFFEDFE9EFB86FD90FBFB" box="[383,624,1024,1050]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">Pomatoschistus bathi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="2ECF4D5E3F7AFFEDFD9FFB86FCB6FBFB" authorityName="Pelagic" baseAuthorityName="de Buen &amp; Fage" baseAuthorityYear="1908" box="[638,854,1024,1050]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Pseudaphya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ferreri">
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F7AFFEDFD9FFB86FCB6FBFB" box="[638,854,1024,1050]" italics="true" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">Pseudaphya ferreri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F7AFFEDFF26FBA2FEB6FB83" blockId="79.[151,1437,520,1194]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">
Habitat. Infralittoral and circalittoral species, on coarse sand close to rocky reefs at depths of 
<quantity id="2E379B383F7AFFEDFB04FBA2FAA9FBDE" box="[1253,1353,1060,1087]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.1" metricValueMin="2.9" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" unit="m" value="35.0" valueMax="41.0" valueMin="29.0">29–41 m</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F7AFFEDFAB9FBA2FEAAFB83" author="Engin, S. &amp; Seyhan, D." pageId="79" pageNumber="80" pagination="1208 - 1223" refId="ref53814" refString="Engin, S. &amp; Seyhan, D. (2017) A new species of Pomatoschistus (Teleostei, Gobiidae): the Mediterraneans smallest marine fish. Journal of Fish Biology, 91, 1208 - 1223. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jfb. 13455" type="journal article" year="2017">Engin &amp; Seyhan 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F7AFFEDFF26FBEAFE49FB4B" blockId="79.[151,1437,520,1194]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80">
Geographic distribution. Eastern Mediterranean. Known only from the northern coast of the Levantine Sea (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F7AFFEDFF7EFB16FE7EFB4B" author="Engin, S. &amp; Seyhan, D." box="[159,414,1168,1194]" pageId="79" pageNumber="80" pagination="1208 - 1223" refId="ref53814" refString="Engin, S. &amp; Seyhan, D. (2017) A new species of Pomatoschistus (Teleostei, Gobiidae): the Mediterraneans smallest marine fish. Journal of Fish Biology, 91, 1208 - 1223. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / jfb. 13455" type="journal article" year="2017">Engin &amp; Seyhan 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
